# agentmemory runs on the LOCAL PC — NOT on the Pi

agentmemory (`@agentmemory/agentmemory`) is an npm package installed **globally on the Windows development machine** (this PC). Its engine, viewer, REST API, logs, config, and all data live locally.

## Hard rule

- **Never SSH into `ar-local-pi5` or any Pi host for agentmemory work.**
- Never treat the Pi as the agentmemory host.
- Never run agentmemory CLI commands over SSH.

## Locations (all local/Windows)

| Resource | Path |
|----------|------|
| Config / data | `C:\Users\jkoka\.agentmemory\` |
| REST API | `http://localhost:3111` (local only) |
| CLI | `agentmemory` (globally installed on Windows) |

## Rationale

agentmemory is a developer-side memory tool, not a Pi service. The Pi hosts the CDR dashboard (`cdr_dashboard_server.py`) and ingest jobs only. Any task involving agentmemory status, memory recall, memory save, config, or logs must target the local Windows machine.
